Boil a full kettle for the macaroni.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with
@salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the @macaroni{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until
tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through
to stop it sticking together. Set aside.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Trim the @mini cucumber{3}(trimmed) and slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @chorizo{90%g}(diced) and fry until starting to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Next, add the garlic and fry, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, @creme fraiche{150%g},
cooked pasta and @water for the sauce{75%ml}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the
heat to medium.

Stir in the @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}(see ingredients for amount - add less if
you'd prefer things milder) and both the grated Cheddar and @grated hard Italian
style cheese{40%g}.

Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Taste and season with salt
and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Share the mac & cheese between your #bowls{}.

Serve the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and cucumber alongside and drizzle over the
@balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!

> This Simple Stovetop Veggie 'Nduja Chorizo Mac & Cheese will be on your table in
> less than 25 minutes. Featuring a hot, umami blend of Calabrian chillies and
> peppers, this 'Nduja is completely meat-free but with all the same flavour.